# 3. Quick Sort

* Quick Sort is a fast sorting algorithm.
* Uses Divide and Conquer method.
* Selects a pivot element.
* Partitions array around pivot.
* Smaller elements move left of pivot.
* Larger elements move right of pivot.
* Average Time Complexity: O(n log n).

Quick Sort divides the array using a pivot element and recursively sorts the partitions. It is widely used
because of its speed and efficiency. Unlike Merge Sort, Quick Sort works in-place and requires less extra
memory. However, worst-case complexity can become O(n²) if pivot selection is poor.

### Example

```python id="pv5x6d"
arr = [8,4,2,9,1]

Pivot = 4

Left  = [2,1]
Right = [8,9]
```

