# 4. Binary Search

* Binary Search is a searching algorithm.
* Works only on sorted arrays.
* Uses Divide and Conquer strategy.
* Repeatedly divides search space into halves.
* Compares target with middle element.
* Faster than linear search.
* Time Complexity: O(log n).

Binary Search efficiently finds an element in a sorted array by repeatedly checking the middle element. If the target
is smaller, search continues in the left half; otherwise, it moves to the right half. This process continues until 
the element is found or the search space becomes empty. Binary Search is widely used because of its fast performance.

### Example

```python id="f95zsn"
arr = [1,3,5,7,9]

Search = 7

Middle Element = 5

Search moves to right half
```

