# 5. Strassen Matrix Multiplication

* Strassen Algorithm is used for matrix multiplication.
* Uses Divide and Conquer approach.
* Divides matrices into smaller submatrices.
* Reduces number of multiplications.
* Faster than normal matrix multiplication.
* Useful for large matrices.
* Time Complexity: O(n^2.81).

Strassen Matrix Multiplication improves matrix multiplication efficiency by reducing multiplication operations. Instead 
of performing 8 multiplications like the traditional method, it performs only 7 multiplications recursively.
This reduces overall computation time and improves performance for large matrices. It is widely used in scientific
computing and graphics applications.

